717967f-c.title: Manhattan: Cabrini Boulevard - 181st Street (West)
717967f-c.text:
Cabrini Boulevard, west side, north of W. 181st Street, showing
the Dr. Chas. V. Paterno estate being cleared. Under demolition are
the greenhouses and the castle-like home of this real-estate operator.
The latter, constructed in 1908 at a cost of ~500,000 is of Roman and
English architecture. A modern apartment house similar to Doctor
Paterno's adjacent Hudson View Garden Apartments will be erected here
at a reported cost of '6,000,000. Note the close proximity of the
George Washington Bridge which is slightly to the S.W. of this location.
August 23, 1938.
Views 1,2 and 3.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
